        },
        "subject": "LU-2177 ptlrpc: flock/posix lock cause LBUGs because of a race",
        "message": "LU-2177 ptlrpc: flock/posix lock cause LBUGs because of a race\n\nThe below races may happen when evicting clients\n\n- LBUG in ldlm_flock_decref_internal_nolock()\n1) A therad calls ldlm_flock_completion_ast()\n2) Another thread is dealing with client eviction and sets some flags\n   to the same flock as (2), and calls ldlm_flock_completion_ast()\n\nBecause of the flags which've been set at (2), the both completion\nast call ldlm_lock_decref_internal() but it's more than necessary\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\n- LBUG in ldlm_lock_destroy()\n1) a flock has been granted\n2) the client which (1)'s flock belongs to is evicted and the flock\n   gets LDLM_FL_FAILED flag\n3) (1)'s thread goes ahead and calls ldlm_process_flock_lock()\n\nBecause of (2), an error is detected and ldlm_flock_destroy() is\ncalled in ldlm_process_flock_lock(). But LDLM_FL_FAILED has already\nbeen set, So ldlm_flock_destroy() never call ldlm_lock_decref_internal\n_nolock() thought it's needed\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nChange-Id: I0428f7807f410f3f4bd45474330741e216ab202f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
